BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:uZirLYHP5JuFDw1Qm5rkY
SUMMARY:March Madness Watch Party at Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill
DTSTAMP:20260327T071009Z
DTSTART:20260404T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Five Iron Golf is your College Basketball HQ this March! Gather
	 your crew and book 1–2 simulator bays for up to 12 people \\(6 people per
	 bay\\) for a bracket-busting watch party experience. Enjoy all-day TV cov
	erage of college basketball alongside cutting-edge golf and multisport sim
	ulators\, a locally-inspired menu\, and custom beverage packages.\n\nBook 
	your watch party for March 19 or 20 and you'll automatically be entered to
	 win a 20-person happy hour with drinks and appetizers — a $1\,000 value!\
	n\nGroup packages can include reserved event space\, team-specific décor\,
	 a dedicated staff member\, full-screen and/or picture-in-picture viewing\
	, a customizable menu\, beverage packages\, free club rentals\, multisport
	 simulators\, and table games. Select the "Small Event" option at booking 
	to ensure simulator bays are placed side-by-side. Availability of select f
	eatures varies by location.\n\nPromotions:\n\nHappy Hour – "It's 5i o'Cloc
	k Somewhere" \\(Monday–Friday\, 3–6 PM\\)\n\nEnjoy $5 bottomless boneless 
	wings\, $10 bottomless bone-in wings\, $5 select beers/cans/cocktails\, $5
	 dips \\(guacamole\, hot honey ricotta\, hummus\\)\, half-off pizzas\, and
	 $5 featured shots. Dine-in only at participating locations\; simulator re
	ntal may be required.\n\n5i After Dark – "Swing In\, For Less"  \\(Sunday–
	Thursday 9 PM to close | Friday–Saturday 10 PM to close\\)\n\nFeatures $29
	/hr simulator rentals plus the same great food and drink specials as Happy
	 Hour\, with wings priced per dozen rather than bottomless. Dine-in only a
	t participating locations\; simulator rental may be required.\n\nhttps://s
	eatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party-at-five-iro
	n-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-04-04T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Food
	 & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party
	-at-five-iron-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-04-04T00
LOCATION:Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill\, 1525 11th Ave Suite 100\, 
	Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT12H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:OjpNjph2j0aUtCqlggEmY
SUMMARY:Rainbow Elder Breakfast
DTSTAMP:20260327T071009Z
DTSTART:20260404T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description We cherish our LGBTQ\\+ elders and believe that mag
	ical and meaningful connections can happen at any age. These breakfasts gi
	ve folks 50\\+ a chance to connect with each other\, eat good food and enj
	oy a morning boost of community that the Eastside has been long overdue fo
	r. Pride Across the Bridge is partnering with the marvelous Sno-Valley Sen
	ior Center to create this space. We meet on the first Saturday of each mon
	th at different locations on the Eastside from 10:30am-12pm. This is a fre
	e to attend event with food and drink available for purchase\, but not req
	uired! If you would like assistance with paying for a bill\, please let ou
	r facilitator know. Financial barriers should not be the hurdle to you enj
	oyably connecting with your community. Contact us for any questions or to 
	RSVP: Info@PrideAcrossTheBridge.org or \\(971\\) 380-5873 Guidelines: This
	 is a safe space for all. Any behavior that goes against the 2SLGBTQIA\\+ 
	and BIPOC community will result in an individual being asked to leave. Fee
	l free to bring friends/family if they will make you more comfortable. Car
	egivers are welcome to join in! Confidentiality Policy: PAB is dedicated t
	o creating a safe and inclusive space for our 2SLGBTQIA\\+ elders. All sha
	red information within the group\, including gender identity\, sexual orie
	ntation\, and personal experiences\, must remain confidential and not be d
	isclosed without explicit consent. Members have the right to anonymity\, a
	nd no one should feel pressured to reveal personal details. By participati
	ng\, members agree to adhere to this policy. April 4th 2026 - Carnation Ca
	fe: 4760 Tolt Ave\, Carnation\, WA\, United States\, Washington Local Tran
	sit: Bus: Snoqualmie Valley Transportation\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com
	/events/#/details/rainbow-elder-breakfast/18425342/2026-04-04T00\n\nFrom S
	EAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/rainbow-elder-breakfast/1
	8425342/2026-04-04T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
